Splitter CLI

Usage: splitter-cli <COMMAND>

Commands:
  devices    List available audio input and output devices
  send       Capture audio from a local device and send it over UDP as Opus packets
  recv       Receive Opus packets over UDP and play them on a local output device
  loop       Capture from a local mic and play back on a local output device (loopback test)
  discover   Discover Splitter peers on the local network via mDNS
  daemon     Start the Splitter background daemon (signaling server + device watcher)
  stream     Open or manage peer-to-peer audio streams (requires a running daemon)
  stats      Show real-time statistics for active streams
  logs       Inspect application logs
  settings   Read or write application settings
  autostart  Manage autostart (login item / systemd user service / Windows Run key)
  metrics    Enable, disable, or check the Prometheus metrics endpoint
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
